  "title": "Video by caitofalltraits",
  "description": "Would you go to Damansara, KL just for this?\n\nPeople often think local food is limited to whatever originated from a country, but as a Singaporean, I know that’s not true. There are local takes on so many different cuisines from around the world - and thank goodness for that!\n\nWhich is why I hate the use of the word ‘authentic’ to describe food (I have a story about this that I will share when I’m in NYC this March), but other than that, I love being able to enjoy all sorts of cuisines done well, like this one particular dish from @uokatsu.malaysia \n\n📍 Malaysia, Federal Territory of Kuala Lumpur, Kuala Lumpur, Sri Hartamas, Jalan Sri Hartamas 1, B-0-7, Ground Floor Plaza Damas 3\n\nEnjoy!",
